"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows one or more categories under a main category to be assigned to the tracker item.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>parentId,inputtype,selectall,descendants,help</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 12,radio,1\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[parentId]</strong> is the ID of the main category, categories in the list will be children of this;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[inputtype]</strong> is one of [d|m|radio|checkbox], where d is a drop-down list, m is a multiple-selection drop-down list, radio and checkbox are self-explanatory;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[selectall]</strong> will provide a checkbox to automatically select all categories in the list if set to 1, default is 0;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[descendants]</strong> All descendant categories (not just first level children) will be included if set to 1, default is 0;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[help]</strong> will display the description in a popup in the input if set to 1, default is 0; only for checkbox or radio\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows one or more categories under a main category to be assigned to the tracker item. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>parentId,inputtype,selectall,descendants,help</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 12,radio,1 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[parentId]</strong> is the ID of the main category, categories in the list will be children of this; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[inputtype]</strong> is one of [d|m|radio|checkbox], where d is a drop-down list, m is a multiple-selection drop-down list, radio and checkbox are self-explanatory; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[selectall]</strong> will provide a checkbox to automatically select all categories in the list if set to 1, default is 0; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[descendants]</strong> All descendant categories (not just first level children) will be included if set to 1, default is 0; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[help]</strong> will display the description in a popup in the input if set to 1, default is 0; only for checkbox or radio \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows user to upload an image into the tracker item.\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>xListSize,yListSize,xDetailsSize,yDetailsSize,uploadLimitScale,shadowBox</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 30,30,100,100,1000,item\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[xListSize]</strong> sets the pixel width of the image in the list view;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[yListSize]</strong> sets the pixel height of the image in the list view;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[xDetailSize]</strong> sets the pixel width of the image in the item view;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[yDetailSize]</strong> sets the pixel height of the image in the item view;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[uploadLimitScale]</strong> sets the maximum total size of the image, in pixels (width or height);\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[shadowbox]</strong> actives a shadowbox(if feature on) = 'item': to use the same shadowbox for an item, ='individual': to use a shadowbox only for this image, other value= to set the group of images of the shadowbox ;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>images are stored in img/trackers;\n\t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Allows user to upload an image into the tracker item. \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>xListSize,yListSize,xDetailsSize,yDetailsSize,uploadLimitScale,shadowBox</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: 30,30,100,100,1000,item \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[xListSize]</strong> sets the pixel width of the image in the list view; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[yListSize]</strong> sets the pixel height of the image in the list view; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[xDetailSize]</strong> sets the pixel width of the image in the item view; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[yDetailSize]</strong> sets the pixel height of the image in the item view; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[uploadLimitScale]</strong> sets the maximum total size of the image, in pixels (width or height); \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[shadowbox]</strong> actives a shadowbox(if feature on) = 'item': to use the same shadowbox for an item, ='individual': to use a shadowbox only for this image, other value= to set the group of images of the shadowbox ; \t\t\t\t<dd>images are stored in img/trackers; \t\t\t\t<dd>multiple options must appear in the order specified, separated by commas. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Display a field value from a specific user in LDAP\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>filter,field,dsn</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: (&(mail=%field_name%)(objectclass=posixaccount)),displayName, authldap\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[filter]</strong> LDAP Filter, without commas. %field_name% can be used, and will be replaced by the tracker field %field_name% current value.;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[field]</strong> LDAP returned field;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[dsn]</strong> DSN name in Tiki;\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Display a field value from a specific user in LDAP \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>filter,field,dsn</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: (&(mail=%field_name%)(objectclass=posixaccount)),displayName, authldap \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[filter]</strong> LDAP Filter, without commas. %field_name% can be used, and will be replaced by the tracker field %field_name% current value.; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[field]</strong> LDAP returned field; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[dsn]</strong> DSN name in Tiki; \t\t\t\t</dl>",
"<dl>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Displays the result of a webservice call\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>service,template,parameter</strong>\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Example: list_books,book_template,order=name_desc&limit=10\n\t\t\t\t<dt>Description:\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[service]</strong> The service name, from the Tiki webservice admin;\n\t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[template]</strong> The template name;\n                                <dd><strong>[params]</strong> List of parameters, formated like a query. %field_name% can be used, and will be replaced by the tracker field %field_name% current value.\n\t\t\t\t</dl>" => "<dl> \t\t\t\t<dt>Function: Displays the result of a webservice call \t\t\t\t<dt>Usage: <strong>service,template,parameter</strong> \t\t\t\t<dt>Example: list_books,book_template,order=name_desc&limit=10 \t\t\t\t<dt>Description: \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[service]</strong> The service name, from the Tiki webservice admin; \t\t\t\t<dd><strong>[template]</strong> The template name;                                 <dd><strong>[params]</strong> List of parameters, formated like a query. %field_name% can be used, and will be replaced by the tracker field %field_name% current value. \t\t\t\t</dl>",
